# RPG Java conventions

## Package layout

```
dev.daniel730.rpgserver
├── RpgServerPlugin
├── hook/          # CivsHook, AuraSkillsHook, VaultHook, LuckPermsHook, PlaceholderHook
├── quest/         # QuestManager, QuestDefinition, listeners
└── progression/   # SkillTreeManager, Archetype, PlayerProfile
```

## Hook pattern

- One class per external plugin; implement `Hook` interface with `enable()` / `disable()` / `isAvailable()`.
- Register Civs/AuraSkills listeners inside hook `enable()`, not in main class.
- Async only for file I/O (player profile YAML); Bukkit API on main thread.

## AuraSkills access

```java
// ✅ after SkillsLoadEvent
SkillsUser user = AuraSkillsApi.get().getUser(uuid);
user.addSkillXp(Skill.FIGHTING, amount);

// ❌ in onEnable before SkillsLoadEvent
```

## Stat modifiers for perks

```java
user.addStatModifier(new StatModifier("rpg_berserk", Stats.STRENGTH, 2.0, Operation.ADD));
// always remove with same id on perk revoke
```

## Minimal diffs

Match surrounding style. No NMS. Prefer events over polling managers.
